{
  "text": "One of the main results of [CITATION_1] is that for any non-elementary hyperbolic group and any \u03a8 the set S(\u03a8) is infinite, i. e. S(\u03a8) = \u221e. Thus, this result says: any non-elementary hyperbolic group is an S \u221e -group. On the other hand, finite and finitely generated Abelian groups are evidently non S \u221e -groups.",
